[I] KDE Frameworks integration module for DNS-SD services (Zeroconf)

[T] KDNSSD is a library for handling the DNS-based Service Discovery Protocol
[T] (DNS-SD), the layer of Zeroconf that allows network services, such as
[T] printers, to be discovered without any user intervention or centralized
[T] infrastructure.

